  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "The legal system addresses money laundering through various mechanisms:\n\n1. Investigation techniques\n- Financial transaction tracking\n- Forensic accounting\n- Collaboration between law enforcement agencies\n- Electronic surveillance\n- International cooperation\n\n2. Legal frameworks\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs)\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture laws\n\n3. Prosecution strategies\n- Charging complex financial crimes\n- Targeting multiple layers of criminal networks\n- Using specialized financial crime units\n- Gathering comprehensive evidence\n\n4. International cooperation\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Coordinated investigations\n- Extradition agreements\n\n5. Financial institution responsibilities\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Internal compliance programs\n- Due diligence procedures\n- Risk assessment mechanisms\n\nThese approaches aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute sophisticated money laundering operations through comprehensive legal and financial strategies.",
